Project Whiteboard Plan: 4dtakki Game Development

This plan outlines the core infrastructure and monetization features required for the next phase of 4dtakki.
1. User Authentication & Profile Management

Objective: Establish persistent user identity and personalization.

    User Login System: Implement a secure authentication flow (e.g., Firebase Auth or Google Identity Services) to sync progress across devices.

    User Avatar System:

        Initialize with 5 Basic Avatar Images unlocked by default.

        Support for "Avatar Packs" within the shop.

        Tiered Pricing: Standard packs vs. Premium/Complex packs with increasing credit costs.

2. Economy & Currency System

Objective: Create a closed-loop economy to drive engagement and monetization.

    In-Game Currency: Implementation of a "Coins/Credits/Chips" system.

    Earning Mechanics:

        Performance-Based: Fixed credit rewards for game wins.

        Ad-Based: Integration of Google AdMob (or relevant Google Cloud developer resources) to provide "Rewarded Ads" for supplemental credits.

3. Progression & Difficulty Scaling

Objective: Gating content to encourage currency spend and replayability.

    Difficulty Locking:

        Easy Mode: Unlocked for all users at start.

        Medium/Hard/Expert: Locked by default.

    Unlock Flow: Users must spend in-game credits to permanently unlock higher difficulty tiers.

4. Customization Shop (The "Marketplace")

Objective: Provide aesthetic sinks for accumulated currency.

    Player Color Customization: Individual purchase options for game-piece or UI highlights.

    Gameplay Themes: * Individual Assets: Background images or specific UI skins available for lower credit amounts.

        Theme Packs: Bundled sets (Background + Colors + UI) available at a premium "Full Pack" price.

5. Technical Implementation Checklist

    [ ] Setup Virtual Environment and Project Dependencies.

    [ ] Integrate AdMob SDK and configure Reward Callbacks.

    [ ] Design Database Schema for User Profiles (JSON/NoSQL) to track owned assets.

    [ ] Implement Shop UI with conditional "Purchase/Equip" logic.
